    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 996.2-generation Carrera is powered by the 3.6L M96/03 flat-six, utilizing VarioCam Plus to produce a linear 320hp. Power is delivered via a G96 6-speed manual transaxle with a factory short-shift kit. Mechanically, the car is sorted: the IMS bearing has been addressed with an LN Engineering retrofit, and the RMS and water pump have been replaced. The suspension features upgraded Bilstein dampers and refreshed polyurethane bushings, maintaining the precise geometry of the multi-link rear setup. Braking is handled by four-piston monobloc calipers over cross-drilled rotors, showing minimal lip. While the finish shows minor road-rash consistent with 'good' driver status, the drivetrain remains tight and the throttle response is sharp. A perfect entry for the enthusiast seeking mechanical substance over a garage-queen pedigree.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 31
    },
    {
